# Helm (microservices) + Istio — interview notes

Use with **`K8S_PLATFORM_ENGINEERING_GUIDE.md`** (Istio section) and **`K8S_MANIFEST_SAMPLES.md`**.

---

## 1. Helm in one minute

**Helm** packages Kubernetes YAML into a **Chart**: versioned, parameterized (`values.yaml`), installable with `helm install` / `helm upgrade`.

| Piece | Role |
|-------|------|
| **`Chart.yaml`** | Chart name, version, appVersion, dependencies (optional). |
| **`values.yaml`** | Default config — image tag, replicas, env, resources, **per-env overrides**. |
| **`templates/`** | Go templates (`{{ .Values.replicaCount }}`) → rendered manifests. |
| **`templates/_helpers.tpl`** | Reusable template snippets (labels, names). |
| **`charts/`** | Subcharts (dependencies unpacked here when using umbrella chart). |

**Why teams use it:** same chart for **dev/stage/prod** by swapping **`values.dev.yaml`** / **`values.prod.yaml`**; CI runs `helm upgrade --install` with `-f values.$ENV.yaml`.

