## 2. Microservices — common folder structures

### Option A — **One chart per service** (most common at scale)

Each repo (or mono-repo folder) owns **one** deployable unit.

```text
services/
├── order-service/
│   └── chart/
│       ├── Chart.yaml
│       ├── values.yaml
│       ├── values.dev.yaml
│       ├── values.prod.yaml
│       └── templates/
│           ├── deployment.yaml
│           ├── service.yaml
│           ├── hpa.yaml
│           ├── serviceaccount.yaml
│           └── _helpers.tpl
├── payment-service/
│   └── chart/
│       └── ...
└── api-gateway/
    └── chart/
        └── ...
```

**Interview line:** *“Each microservice has its own Helm chart and lifecycle; teams release independently.”*

---

### Option B — **Mono-repo with `charts/` at root**

```text
my-platform/
├── charts/
│   ├── order/
│   ├── payment/
│   └── gateway/
├── environments/
│   ├── dev/
│   │   └── order-values.yaml    # overrides only what differs
│   └── prod/
│       └── order-values.yaml
└── README.md
```

Deploy: `helm upgrade --install order ./charts/order -n orders -f environments/prod/order-values.yaml`

---

### Option C — **Umbrella chart** (meta-chart that bundles subcharts)

```text
platform/
├── Chart.yaml          # dependencies: order, payment (tgz or repo URL)
├── values.yaml         # global + per-subchart: order: {...}, payment: {...}
└── charts/             # populated by `helm dependency update`
```

**`Chart.yaml` snippet:**

```yaml
apiVersion: v2
name: platform
version: 1.0.0
dependencies:
  - name: order
    version: "1.x"
    repository: "file://../charts/order"
  - name: payment
    version: "1.x"
    repository: "file://../charts/payment"
```

**When to say umbrella:** *“We use it for a **single** `helm install` of the whole product in demo/staging; prod often still deploys **per-service** charts for independent releases.”*

---

### Option D — **GitOps (Argo CD / Flux)**

- Helm chart lives in Git; **Argo CD Application** points to path + value file.
- **Folder structure** same as A/B; extra **`Application.yaml`** (Argo) per env.

